# Home Assistant add-ons run on Linux. Files baked into the container
# image (shell scripts, nginx config, templates) MUST use LF endings:
# a CRLF in a shebang makes the kernel look for an interpreter that does
# not exist (e.g. "/bin/sh\r"), so the container fails to start with
# "/tmp/entrypoint.sh: not found" (exit 127). Forcing eol=lf here keeps
# Windows checkouts/edits from reintroducing CRLF.
*.sh    text eol=lf
*.conf  text eol=lf
*.gtpl  text eol=lf
*.types text eol=lf
